And as we'll talk about soon,
我们很快也会讲到

523
00:33:04,420 --> 00:33:05,870
a person who is committed to excellence,
追求卓越的人

524
00:33:06,060 --> 00:33:09,560
not only does he or she not give up on the journey
不仅仅不会放弃整个旅途

525
00:33:11,610 --> 00:33:14,180
or rather on the outcome,
或者结果

526
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:18,830
they actually reach higher levels of performance.
他们常常会获得更高的成就

527
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:22,410
But we'll get to that soon.
我们很快就会讲到

528
00:33:22,820 --> 00:33:24,340
A person committed to excellence
追求卓越的人

529
00:33:24,570 --> 00:33:26,400
is not just about temporary relief,
并不只关注短时间的放松

530
00:33:26,610 --> 00:33:28,390
but about lasting satisfaction.
还关注长久的满足

531
00:33:28,620 --> 00:33:31,850
Yes,she has the ups and downs like we all do.
是的 生活中会有起起伏伏

532
00:33:32,080 --> 00:33:36,080
However,also able to enjoy the journey day to day-
但是 也能够享受旅途中的每一天

533
00:33:36,310 --> 00:33:37,830
the experience being the college,
在大学里的经历

534
00:33:38,040 --> 00:33:41,310
the experience of having a lovely meal with my friends,
和朋友们美美地吃了一餐的经历

535
00:33:41,570 --> 00:33:47,790
the experience of reading and being exposed to great writers,
阅读名家的作品的经历

536
00:33:50,380 --> 00:33:55,870
to interesting classes,to nice extra curricular activities,
上有趣的课 参加有趣的课外活动的经历

537
00:33:56,130 --> 00:33:59,410
and appreciating it,not taking it for granted,
并且重视这样的经历 而不是忽略它们

538
00:33:59,650 --> 00:34:02,310
not seeing it as just incidental-
不是把这些看做普通的

539
00:34:02,530 --> 00:34:04,240
just something that I need to get through
为了成功的最终目的

540
00:34:04,430 --> 00:34:07,200
in order to get to where I really want to get to.
我必须经历的事情

541
00:34:08,340 --> 00:34:10,160
Well,you may want to get...really want to get there,
你或许会非常渴望成功

542
00:34:10,340 --> 00:34:12,780
but where you really are is here and now.
但是你所在的却是此时 此地

543
00:34:13,010 --> 00:34:14,590
No other place.
不是别处

544
00:34:18,860 --> 00:34:21,340
You know,I haven't met,maybe you have,
你们也知道 我从来没有 或许你们有

545
00:34:21,570 --> 00:34:24,500
but I haven't met the perfect person.
我从来没有遇见过完美的人

546
00:34:26,890 --> 00:34:27,480
I don't think that person exists.
我认为这样的人是不存在的

547
00:34:27,700 --> 00:34:30,930
In other words,if there isn't a person,a perfect person,
换句话说 如果根本就不存在完美的人

548
00:34:31,150 --> 00:34:34,380
for every person,there's inevitable failure.
那么对每个人来说 失败都是不可避免的

549
00:34:36,170 --> 00:34:38,500
And a perfectionist who is obsessed with failure
为失败所困惑的完美主义者

550
00:34:38,670 --> 00:34:42,020
just focuses on that,whereas the person committed to excellence,
只是专注于失败 而追求卓越的人

551
00:34:42,250 --> 00:34:45,150
there is possibility of success every step of the way,
则会发现路途上每一步都有成功的机会

552
00:34:45,370 --> 00:34:47,340
even in failure.
甚至在失败中也有这样的机会

553
00:34:50,250 --> 00:34:52,890
A perfectionist very often wastes time-
完美主义者常常将时间浪费在

554
00:34:53,130 --> 00:34:55,680
has to read every word,every...
必须读清楚每个字

555
00:34:55,910 --> 00:34:58,820
You know,"i have to be dotted,every t crossed."
"我要做到最好 拿满分"

556
00:34:59,210 --> 00:35:00,470
It's all or nothing.
要么全部要么没有

557
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:01,950
Either I hand in a perfect paper,
要么我交上去一份完美的论文

558
00:35:02,150 --> 00:35:04,200
or I don't hand in a paper at all.
要么我就干脆不交论文

559
00:35:05,090 --> 00:35:09,140
Either it's a straight A,or I'm a failure.
要么我就拿到A 要么我就一无是处

560
00:35:11,180 --> 00:35:14,930
All or nothing.And sometimes,it's appropriate.
要么全部要么没有 有时候这是合适的

561
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:16,890
And that's what a person committed to excellence does-
有时候追求卓越的人也会持有这种态度

562
00:35:17,110 --> 00:35:21,440
understands when,for example,
比如

563
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:24,440
if you are a surgeon,you want to have the perfect operation.
如果你是一个医生 你想做一场完美的手术

564
00:35:24,630 --> 00:35:25,910
You don't want to say,"well,it's OK.
你可不会说 "好吧 没关系啊

565
00:35:26,110 --> 00:35:30,720
I'm 80 percent right about where exactly to cut."
我切对了八成应该切的东西"

566
00:35:30,980 --> 00:35:34,080
Yeah,there are places where you want the perfectionism.
没错 在有些场合你会需要完美主义

567
00:35:34,430 --> 00:35:38,560
But in many other areas in our lives,it's not necessary.
但是在我们生活中的其他方面 都不必要

568
00:35:38,810 --> 00:35:44,950
And it hurts us.A perfectionist is very often prone to disorders.
甚至会伤害我们 完美主义者往往倾向混乱

569
00:35:45,180 --> 00:35:47,230
And I mean disorders of numerous times including,
我是指多方面的混乱

570
00:35:47,430 --> 00:35:49,120
for example,eating disorder.
比如进食问题

571
00:35:49,350 --> 00:35:51,250
So let me give you a personal example.
我来给你们提供一个个人的例子吧

572
00:35:51,470 --> 00:35:54,490
So when I was playing squash,when I was playing full time,
在我还在打职业壁球的时候

573
00:35:54,710 --> 00:36:00,430
I had to really take care of my diet- eat healthfully,eat well.
我必须控制我的食谱 要吃得健康吃得好

574
00:36:01,230 --> 00:36:02,100
But there was a problem.
但还是产生了问题

575
00:36:02,300 --> 00:36:04,460
There was a real challenge in my life.
我的生活中有一项重大挑战

576
00:36:04,700 --> 00:36:13,250
And that challenge was my mother who is the perfect cook.
这挑战就是我的母亲个完美的大厨

577
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:17,360
And her cakes are outstanding.
她做的的蛋糕尤其诱人

578
00:36:18,820 --> 00:36:20,610
So here is the common scenario that
于是就有了这样的我在长大的时候

579
00:36:20,810 --> 00:36:24,270
I encountered growing up- tough childhood:
常常遇到的状况 痛苦的童年

580
00:36:24,470 --> 00:36:25,990
I would come home after the squash practice,
我在壁球训练过后回家

581
00:36:26,220 --> 00:36:28,420
open the fridge,starving.
饿得要命地打开冰箱

582
00:36:29,550 --> 00:36:33,020
And there was a large piece of cake.
然后那里面有一大块蛋糕

583
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:35,260
Not a whole cake,but you know a quarter cake,
不是一整个 但差不多四分之一个

584
00:36:35,540 --> 00:36:40,370
very large,so inviting.So alluring.
非常大的一块 实在是非常诱人

585
00:36:40,570 --> 00:36:43,740
And I know from past experiences it's so delicious.
我根据以往的经验知道 这很好吃

586
00:36:44,360 --> 00:36:47,830
I look at it.And then I close the fridge.
我看着这块蛋糕 然后关上了冰箱门

587
00:36:48,030 --> 00:36:49,020
Because I can't have it.
因为我不能吃

588
00:36:49,170 --> 00:36:51,440
I'm in middle of training for an important tournament.
当时我正在在为一个重要的巡回赛训练

589
00:36:52,910 --> 00:36:53,960
But three minutes later,
但是在三分钟以后

590
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:58,020
I go to the fridge again,just to make sure it's still there.
我回到冰箱那看蛋糕还在不在

591
00:36:59,430 --> 00:37:02,720
Why? Those of you who know my brother understand why.
为什么 你们中认识我兄弟的都明白

592
00:37:02,980 --> 00:37:04,470
My brother is much bigger than I am.
我兄弟块头比我大多了

593
00:37:04,670 --> 00:37:07,510
And he likes my mom's cooking no less than I do.
他对我母亲的厨艺的喜爱一点不在我之下

594
00:37:07,720 --> 00:37:10,050
So I was just making sure that it was still there.
所以我去确定蛋糕还在那

595
00:37:10,250 --> 00:37:11,480
And it was.
确实还在

596
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:14,730
And then 10 minutes later,I had to go back because my brother
再过了十分钟 我必须再去检查一遍

597
00:37:14,930 --> 00:37:16,690
had just disappeared from my eyes a few minutes.
因为我兄弟在我视线内消失了几分钟

598
00:37:16,890 --> 00:37:18,570
I thought he went to the fridge.
我以为他到冰箱那去了

599
00:37:20,090 --> 00:37:22,720
So I opened the fridge again and it was still there.
所以我又打开了冰箱一次 蛋糕还在

600
00:37:23,250 --> 00:37:24,580
So I was relieved.
然后我感到一阵轻松

601
00:37:24,830 --> 00:37:27,740
And about 5 minutes later I had to go back to the fridge.
大约五分钟以后我又回到冰箱那里

602
00:37:27,970 --> 00:37:32,150
I opened the door and two minutes later,there was no cake.
我打开冰箱门 两分钟以后蛋糕就不见了

603
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:38,310
All or nothing.Either I don't touch it,or I devour it.
要么全部要么没有 要么我不碰要么我吃完

604
00:37:38,800 --> 00:37:41,720
This is the schema that a perfectionist has.
这就是完美主义者持有的基模

605
00:37:42,210 --> 00:37:48,290
It's not "OK,let me have a slice of it." It's nothing or all.
不会说"好吧 我就吃一块" 要么不吃要么吃完

606
00:37:50,020 --> 00:37:51,970
And this is the schema that perfectionists have:
所以这就是完美主义者的基模

607
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:56,070
either I'm a supermodel or I'm overweight.
我要么成为超级模特 要么超重

608
00:37:57,350 --> 00:37:59,160
All or nothing.And it's destructive.
要么全部要么没有 这是很有破坏力的

609
00:37:59,350 --> 00:38:03,300
It hurts so much on so many levels.
这会对我们产生各个层次的严重伤害

610
00:38:03,550 --> 00:38:07,310
As opposed to the healthy approach.
相对于健康的方式而言

611
00:38:07,570 --> 00:38:09,780
OK,so I'll have a slice.So I'll have a little bit.
好的 我就吃一小块

612
00:38:09,990 --> 00:38:15,260
OK,so I gained a couple of pounds- big deal?! I'm human.
好的 我重了几磅 这算大事吗 我是人

613
00:38:15,590 --> 00:38:23,540
I'm not a machine.I'm not a Barbie.Or Ken.(Laugh)
我不是机器 也不是芭比娃娃 更不是Ken

614
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:28,960
I caught myself there.
我说错话了

615
00:38:32,460 --> 00:38:37,190
Hurts self-esteem.Why? Because...
这很伤自尊 为什么 因为

616
00:38:37,430 --> 00:38:39,020
Nathaniel Branden who writes about self-esteem-
Nathaniel Branden写过很多关于自尊的文字

617
00:38:39,180 --> 00:38:42,100
we'll talk a lot about him in that lecture 3 weeks from now.
我们在未来三周内将会更多地讲到他

618
00:38:43,370 --> 00:38:46,600
The first pillar of self-esteem is self-acceptance.
自尊的第一个基础就是自我接受

619
00:38:47,100 --> 00:38:50,800
And remember a perfectionist does not accept him/herself.
要记得完美主义者是不接受自我的

620
00:38:52,970 --> 00:38:55,700
Second,the reason why it hurts self-esteem- remember,
第二个伤害自尊的原因是

621
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:58,940
there is constant,inevitable failure for a perfectionist
完美主义者总会遇到长期且不可避免的失败

622
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:01,640
because there is no perfect person.And
因为根本就没有完美的人

623
00:39:01,850 --> 00:39:06,130
if I constantly fail or constantly perceive myself as a failure,
而如果我一直失败或者视自己为失败者

624
00:39:06,370 --> 00:39:09,840
am I going to have high self-esteem? Of course not.
那我还会有较高的自尊心吗 当然不会

625
00:39:13,090 --> 00:39:15,340
It also hurts self-esteem because a perfectionist
另一个完美主义者容易自尊心受伤的原因

626
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:19,570
is less likely to try,less like to put him/herself on the line.
是他们更不愿意去尝试

627
00:39:19,800 --> 00:39:22,250
And the price that I pay for that
而如果我不愿意尝试的话 其后果就是

628
00:39:22,470 --> 00:39:25,130
when I don't try is lower level of self-esteem.
更加低的自尊心

629
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:27,200
Remember self-perception theory.
还记得自我知觉理论吗

630
00:39:29,540 --> 00:39:32,260
Versus on-going,continuous improvement.
相对的是持续的自我提升

631
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:36,870
Not a straight line,but a spiral that goes up and up.
不是一条直线直上的 而是旋转向上的

632
00:39:39,260 --> 00:39:41,680
Perfectionism harms relationships.
完美主义伤害人际关系

633
00:39:41,940 --> 00:39:45,430
Again,I just look back and I,you know from this perspective,
回想过去 我从这个角度来说

634
00:39:45,630 --> 00:39:47,600
it's hard for me to fathom the kind of mistakes
我很难捉摸 我基于完美主义

635
00:39:47,750 --> 00:39:51,550
that I have made in relationships based on perfectionism.
在人际关系中所犯的错误的类型

636
00:39:51,770 --> 00:39:54,260
Why? First of all,defensiveness.
为什么 第一 自卫性

637
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:57,880
It is very difficult to form intimacy with some one
如果我一直是处于自卫性的位置

638
00:39:58,160 --> 00:40:02,360
when I'm constantly on the defensive,when I can't accept
如果我不能接受或者处理批评

639
00:40:02,590 --> 00:40:06,380
or do something at the very least with criticisms.
那我就很难和别人形成亲密的关系

640
00:40:06,620 --> 00:40:09,550
What kind of intimacy is possible there?
这样的情况下怎么可能建立亲密关系呢

641
00:40:09,770 --> 00:40:11,460
The other reason why it harms relationships
另一个完美主义伤害人际关系的原因是

642
00:40:11,630 --> 00:40:15,800
is that very often,we mirror...
我们经常

643
00:40:16,050 --> 00:40:19,540
Our approach to the world mirrors our approach toward ourselves.
我们对世界的看法和对自己的看法一样

644
00:40:19,770 --> 00:40:22,380
So if I'm a perfectionist and expect perfectionism-
如果我是完美主义者那我期望的就是完美

645
00:40:22,580 --> 00:40:26,510
a straight line for myself,I would expect the same from others,
对我来说是一条直线 对他人亦是如此

646
00:40:26,730 --> 00:40:27,640
whether it's from my partner,
不论是对于我的伴侣

647
00:40:27,870 --> 00:40:31,160
whether it's later on my children or friends.
还是对我的孩子和朋友

648
00:40:31,380 --> 00:40:32,240
And now as we...
现在我们...

649
00:40:32,460 --> 00:40:35,400
I think- I establish before- there is no perfect person.
我以前也说过了 没有完美的人

650
00:40:35,630 --> 00:40:38,140
Now it may seem perfect when we first meet.
我们第一次见面的时候可能感觉是完美的

651
00:40:38,380 --> 00:40:41,340
And during the honeymoon phase,it is perfect.
在度蜜月的时候 也是完美的

652
00:40:41,550 --> 00:40:43,680
He or she is perfect.
他或她是完美的

653
